the most important thing to you?

518
00:35:32,559 --> 00:35:33,820
Jung Tae,

519
00:35:33,990 --> 00:35:36,070
are you angry you're not allowed
to stay at the camp?

520
00:35:36,329 --> 00:35:37,558
You know how Father is.

521
00:35:37,559 --> 00:35:39,659
He barely gave permission
about you missing school to train...

522
00:35:39,660 --> 00:35:41,400
No, it's not like that.

523
00:35:42,300 --> 00:35:43,800
I'll get going.

524
00:35:46,639 --> 00:35:48,808
I'll come pick you up
before Father gets off work.

525
00:35:48,809 --> 00:35:50,570
Don't come to the camp.

526
00:35:50,979 --> 00:35:52,840
Meet me here instead.

527
00:36:05,990 --> 00:36:08,590
Guys, don't run.

528
00:36:09,090 --> 00:36:11,499
- Ju Bin, you're in Room One.
- Yes, coach.

529
00:36:11,700 --> 00:36:13,499
Kyung Jae, Room One.

530
00:36:14,999 --> 00:36:17,639
- Gun Woo, Room One.
- Yes, coach.

531
00:36:18,499 --> 00:36:20,808
Digestive Drink, Room Four.
Work hard.

532
00:36:20,809 --> 00:36:21,809
Yes, coach.

533
00:36:22,869 --> 00:36:24,909
- Attention.
- Attention!

534
00:36:24,910 --> 00:36:26,578
I can't hear you. Attention!

535
00:36:26,579 --> 00:36:27,708
- Attention!
- Attention!

536
00:36:27,709 --> 00:36:29,879
You have just three minutes.

537
00:36:29,880 --> 00:36:32,118
Go to your rooms and unpack.

538
00:36:32,119 --> 00:36:34,590
Change into training clothes
and get back here.

539
00:36:34,919 --> 00:36:36,289
Ready.

540
00:36:41,630 --> 00:36:44,759
Too slow. Hurry up!

541
00:36:44,760 --> 00:36:45,860
Yes, coach!

542
00:36:59,880 --> 00:37:01,880
Jung Tae, are you in Room Four too?

543
00:37:02,749 --> 00:37:04,780
Just my luck.

544
00:37:06,249 --> 00:37:07,280
Move.

545
00:37:09,990 --> 00:37:11,659
You have one minute left!

546
00:37:11,660 --> 00:37:13,820
There will be a penalty
for the one who comes last.

547
00:37:21,499 --> 00:37:23,169
Guys, hurry.

548
00:37:26,939 --> 00:37:28,368
Hey, Digestive Drink!

549
00:37:28,369 --> 00:37:30,208
What?

550
00:37:30,209 --> 00:37:31,839
Take it off. It's mine.

551
00:37:31,840 --> 00:37:33,938
We all have the same uniform.

552
00:37:33,939 --> 00:37:35,379
Why must you be so fussy?

553
00:37:35,380 --> 00:37:36,410
Hand it over.

554
00:37:37,519 --> 00:37:39,349
Hey, let go!

555
00:37:39,720 --> 00:37:42,749
- Hand it over.
- I said, let go!

556
00:37:42,919 --> 00:37:45,288
- This is mine.
- Hey, let go!

557
00:37:45,289 --> 00:37:48,859
- Stay focused.
- Stay focused.

558
00:37:48,860 --> 00:37:50,659
- Stay focused.
- Stay focused.

559
00:37:50,660 --> 00:37:52,829
- Stay focused.
- Stay focused.

560
00:37:59,800 --> 00:38:02,208
Hey, I can barely hear you.

561
00:38:02,209 --> 00:38:03,938
Do you want to do ten more laps?

562
00:38:03,939 --> 00:38:07,780
Stay focused. Stay focused.

563
00:38:08,209 --> 00:38:12,049
Stay focused. Stay focused.

564
00:38:12,050 --> 00:38:14,050
If you leave it tangled,

565
00:38:14,550 --> 00:38:15,618
it's your loss.

566
00:38:15,619 --> 00:38:17,249
Stay focused.

567
00:38:17,760 --> 00:38:19,759
- Stay focused.
- Stay focused.

568
00:38:19,760 --> 00:38:23,288
Stay focused. Stay focused.

569
00:38:23,289 --> 00:38:26,458
My gosh, Gyeongju Gas sent one too.

570
00:38:26,459 --> 00:38:28,668
I know. There's limited space,

571
00:38:28,669 --> 00:38:30,268
so it'd be better
to leave them here.

572
00:38:30,269 --> 00:38:32,038
- Yes, let's do that.
- That's right.

573
00:38:32,039 --> 00:38:34,709
- Perfect.
- Soo Chan. Everyone's here, right?

574
00:38:35,309 --> 00:38:37,039
I'll get going then.

575
00:38:37,639 --> 00:38:40,979
You brat! Where do you need to go?

576
00:38:41,180 --> 00:38:43,748
You must stay until the end
as a member of the family!

577
00:38:43,749 --> 00:38:46,019
Hey, Auntie is right.

578
00:38:46,349 --> 00:38:48,590
What's going on?
Do you have another date?

579
00:38:49,249 --> 00:38:51,388
What? You have a date?

580
00:38:51,389 --> 00:38:52,888
Why didn't you tell us?

581
00:38:52,889 --> 00:38:56,458
My gosh, Mr. Kim! You made it!

582
00:38:56,459 --> 00:38:57,829
- Thank you for coming.
- Hello.

583
00:38:58,329 --> 00:38:59,800
Gosh, Mr. Hwang!

584
00:39:02,570 --> 00:39:04,769
I'm sorry we're a little late.

585
00:39:09,240 --> 00:39:10,439
Congratulations, Soo Chan.

586
00:39:10,669 --> 00:39:12,509
Gosh, thank you.

587
00:39:12,510 --> 00:39:14,110
Can you take this?

588
00:39:15,180 --> 00:39:16,680
Aren't you guys going on a date?

589
00:39:18,050 --> 00:39:21,650
I guess you came to see her
because you couldn't wait.

590
00:39:23,189 --> 00:39:24,189
Right.

591
00:39:26,289 --> 00:39:27,388
My goodness.

592
00:39:27,389 --> 00:39:29,529
You keep showering me
with such precious gifts.

593
00:39:29,530 --> 00:39:30,559
My gosh.

594
00:39:31,030 --> 00:39:32,759
You gave my son permission
to marry your daughter,

595
00:39:32,760 --> 00:39:34,260
your dearest treasure.

596
00:39:44,479 --> 00:39:45,579
- Myeong Hee.
- Myeong Hee.

597
00:39:45,709 --> 00:39:46,808
- What?
- My gosh.

598
00:39:46,809 --> 00:39:48,529
I didn't know
there would be so many guests.

599
00:39:52,880 --> 00:39:54,150
I had no idea.

600
00:39:56,289 --> 00:39:58,919
My goodness,
you didn't have to bring anything.

601
00:40:05,430 --> 00:40:06,499
Soo Chan.

602
00:40:06,900 --> 00:40:08,829
- Show Mr. Hwang around.
- Right.

603
00:40:09,200 --> 00:40:11,070
I'll be right back. Wait here, okay?

604
00:40:12,400 --> 00:40:13,920
Mr. Hwang,
I'll give you a little tour.

605
00:40:14,539 --> 00:40:15,570
This way, please.

606
00:40:19,979 --> 00:40:21,909
Gosh, Soo Ryeon.

607
00:40:21,910 --> 00:40:24,679
Your husband-to-be is here.
Why are you standing around?

608
00:40:24,680 --> 00:40:26,279
Go make some coffee for him.

609
00:40:26,280 --> 00:40:28,589
Auntie, don't call him like that.

610
00:40:28,590 --> 00:40:30,189
I'll make coffee.

611
00:40:30,590 --> 00:40:31,619
Take a seat.

612
00:40:33,389 --> 00:40:34,660
Yes, take a seat.

613
00:40:34,789 --> 00:40:37,260
Enjoy the food, everyone.

614
00:40:38,599 --> 00:40:41,569
Yes, thank you for coming.

615
00:40:41,570 --> 00:40:44,229
(Changhwa Pharmaceuticals
Aerial View)

616
00:40:46,999 --> 00:40:48,469
You'll buy patented medicines
from other countries...

617
00:40:48,470 --> 00:40:50,070
and manufacture them?

618
00:40:50,610 --> 00:40:52,910
Will this be more profitable
than just importing them?

619
00:40:54,010 --> 00:40:55,309
Yes, of course.

620
00:40:57,349 --> 00:40:58,949
Being able to supply
such medicines on our own...

621
00:40:58,950 --> 00:41:00,880
without having
to rely on importing them...

622
00:41:01,050 --> 00:41:02,789
will help strengthen our country.

623
00:41:04,720 --> 00:41:06,419
You have such an admirable son.

624
00:41:06,959 --> 00:41:08,958
Gosh, he has grand plans...

625
00:41:08,959 --> 00:41:10,260
but has a long way to go.

626
00:41:11,930 --> 00:41:14,469
We underestimated
building a pharmaceutical factory.

627
00:41:14,470 --> 00:41:16,829
It costs a fortune.

628
00:41:19,269 --> 00:41:22,309
One of my in-laws is looking
for a good company to invest in.

629
00:41:22,970 --> 00:41:24,609
Shall I introduce you to him?

630
00:41:24,610 --> 00:41:25,680
Pardon me?

631
00:41:26,010 --> 00:41:28,949
We'd be grateful,
but you don't have to.

632
00:41:28,950 --> 00:41:31,450
This isn't some stranger's business.
We're a family now.

633
00:41:34,180 --> 00:41:36,590
You're the brother
of my future daughter-in-law.

634
00:41:44,189 --> 00:41:45,999
Oh, make two cups of coffee for me.

635
00:41:46,229 --> 00:41:48,300
- No sugar, please.
- Sure.

636
00:41:48,769 --> 00:41:49,800
Hey.

637
00:41:50,700 --> 00:41:51,769
Is that the guy?

638
00:41:51,970 --> 00:41:54,410
Soo Chan's future brother-in-law.
The one born out of wedlock.

639
00:41:56,639 --> 00:41:59,910
He wasn't just born out of wedlock.
His mother was a courtesan.

640
00:42:00,709 --> 00:42:03,110
My gosh,
what is Soo Chan's family thinking?

641
00:42:03,450 --> 00:42:05,578
I understand their daughter
is a troublemaker,

642
00:42:05,579 --> 00:42:07,888
but how could they marry her off
to someone's illegitimate son?

643
00:42:07,889 --> 00:42:10,119
Come on. I heard he's a med student.

644
00:42:10,150 --> 00:42:11,590
And he's good-looking.

645
00:42:11,689 --> 00:42:13,388
He'd better be.

646
00:42:13,389 --> 00:42:15,030
His mother was a courtesan
after all.

647
00:42:15,260 --> 00:42:17,260
Keep it down. He'll hear you.

648
00:42:20,229 --> 00:42:21,530
I was born out of wedlock.

649
00:42:23,869 --> 00:42:25,439
But what's the problem with that?

650
00:42:25,769 --> 00:42:27,368
Thanks to our pasts,
we turned out to be...

651
00:42:27,369 --> 00:42:29,470
strong and interesting people.

652
00:42:35,709 --> 00:42:36,780
My goodness.

653
00:42:37,050 --> 00:42:40,450
If you let this year go by,
it'll be too late.

654
00:42:40,849 --> 00:42:42,949
There's a right time for everything.

655
00:42:42,950 --> 00:42:44,558
You won't be
an eligible bachelorette forever.

656
00:42:44,559 --> 00:42:45,958
Why would you put it off?

657
00:42:45,959 --> 00:42:48,729
- Here's your coffee.
- Thank you.

658
00:42:48,829 --> 00:42:51,530
- Stop it.
- Miss, are you a bookkeeper?

659
00:42:52,329 --> 00:42:53,630
No, I'm Soo Ryeon's friend.

660
00:42:54,300 --> 00:42:56,768
My gosh.
You kept making coffee over there,

661
00:42:56,769 --> 00:42:58,499
so I thought you worked
at a coffee shop.

662
00:42:59,300 --> 00:43:01,470
Don't get me wrong.
It's because you're pretty.

663
00:43:02,010 --> 00:43:04,208
- Did you go to college together?
- Listen to me.

664
00:43:04,209 --> 00:43:05,439
Do you have a boyfriend?

665
00:43:08,110 --> 00:43:09,209
She's my guest.

666
00:43:13,550 --> 00:43:14,590
Really?

667
00:43:15,889 --> 00:43:18,389
Myeong Hee, let's go.
I'll take you home.

668
00:43:19,260 --> 00:43:20,260
Come on.

669
00:43:28,800 --> 00:43:29,970
Enjoy the coffee.

670
00:43:33,599 --> 00:43:34,639
I'm off.

671
00:43:39,410 --> 00:43:41,179
We should get going too, ma'am.

672
00:43:41,180 --> 00:43:42,749
- Shall we?
- Oh, okay.

673
00:43:42,950 --> 00:43:44,919
- See you.
- Okay, see you.

674
00:43:59,059 --> 00:44:01,800
You should never force yourself
to do what you're not used to.

675
00:44:03,570 --> 00:44:05,845
If I keep forcing myself like this,
I may actually fall ill.

676
00:44:05,869 --> 00:44:07,169
Let's end this here.

677
00:44:07,869 --> 00:44:08,939
What?

678
00:44:09,939 --> 00:44:11,679
Hey, you're also...

679
00:44:11,680 --> 00:44:12,680
I'll give you three days.

680
00:44:13,079 --> 00:44:15,479
Whether you tell the truth
or another lie,

681
00:44:15,680 --> 00:44:17,380
do what it takes
to deal with your family.

682
00:44:17,849 --> 00:44:19,749
If we take this further,
we can't get out of it.

683
00:44:21,919 --> 00:44:23,450
What if I say no?

684
00:44:25,959 --> 00:44:27,419
Then I'll do whatever I want.

685
00:44:40,800 --> 00:44:42,070
What? Med school?

686
00:44:42,740 --> 00:44:45,679
Myeong Hee, I'm so impressed.

687
00:44:45,680 --> 00:44:47,280
It's nothing impressive.

688
00:44:47,579 --> 00:44:50,808
The med schools here only admit
those who will become doctors,

689
00:44:50,809 --> 00:44:52,748
whereas everyone gets admitted
in Germany,

690
00:44:52,749 --> 00:44:54,380
but few survive.

691
00:44:54,950 --> 00:44:56,670
I have to do a good job
once I start school.

692
00:44:56,820 --> 00:44:58,940
People who are overly modest
can be annoying, you see.

693
00:45:02,130 --> 00:45:03,590
So when do you leave?

694
00:45:04,590 --> 00:45:06,599
In a month. That's the plan now.

695
00:45:07,059 --> 00:45:09,369
What? In a month?

696
00:45:10,430 --> 00:45:13,939
It all depends on the situation,
so it might change,

697
00:45:15,209 --> 00:45:16,329
but that's the plan for now.

698
00:45:16,809 --> 00:45:19,078
That's too soon...

699
00:45:19,079 --> 00:45:21,849
I mean, that's soon.

700
00:45:22,579 --> 00:45:24,410
A month will fly by.

701
00:45:27,079 --> 00:45:29,519
What? You have a gray hair.

702
00:45:29,990 --> 00:45:31,919
What? I do?

703
00:45:32,220 --> 00:45:33,789
Hold on. Let me pluck it.

704
00:45:44,669 --> 00:45:45,900
Let's go, shall we?

705
00:46:04,860 --> 00:46:05,889
Myeong Hee...

706
00:46:07,090 --> 00:46:08,459
Hold him down.

707
00:46:12,130 --> 00:46:13,430
You idiots.

708
00:46:14,970 --> 00:46:16,930
I told you to interrogate him,
not butcher him.

709
00:46:17,599 --> 00:46:18,799
Who will take responsibility
if things go south...

710
00:46:18,800 --> 00:46:19,999
in this day and age?

711
00:46:20,039 --> 00:46:21,139
We're sorry, sir.

712
00:46:22,740 --> 00:46:25,280
Sir, please spare me.

713
00:46:25,740 --> 00:46:26,840
Don't kill me!

714
00:46:28,650 --> 00:46:29,979
Sit up!

715
00:46:30,910 --> 00:46:34,079
Please, sir...
I really didn't do anything wrong.

716
00:46:35,619 --> 00:46:36,689
Hey.

717
00:46:41,360 --> 00:46:43,589
I really didn't do anything wrong!

718
00:46:43,590 --> 00:46:46,130
I did nothing wrong!

719
00:46:47,130 --> 00:46:48,169
Dad.

720
00:46:52,200 --> 00:46:53,699
Please believe me! I didn't...

721
00:46:53,700 --> 00:46:56,039
- I'm sorry, sir. We'll quickly...
- Forget it.

722
00:46:56,740 --> 00:46:58,110
Have someone tail him.

723
00:46:59,110 --> 00:47:01,609
The student council executive?
We're already on it.

724
00:47:01,610 --> 00:47:02,650
No.

725
00:47:03,680 --> 00:47:04,820
My son.

726
00:47:07,479 --> 00:47:10,749
(Gwangju Pyeonghwa Hospital,
Emergency Room)

727
00:47:12,619 --> 00:47:14,660
My goodness,
I'm in the main sector again.

728
00:47:17,630 --> 00:47:19,530
It's already May.

729
00:47:20,130 --> 00:47:21,669
Time really flies.

730
00:47:50,860 --> 00:47:52,660
(I'll pass the exam this year
no matter what!)

731
00:47:56,999 --> 00:47:58,030
Goodness.

732
00:47:58,439 --> 00:48:00,638
Darn, a year has passed already...

733
00:48:00,639 --> 00:48:02,840
but I can still smell
my brother's stink.

734
00:48:03,840 --> 00:48:05,110
Dad!

735
00:48:06,579 --> 00:48:08,308
- Dad!
- What?

736
00:48:08,309 --> 00:48:11,109
- Dad.
- What is it? I'm busy.

737
00:48:11,110 --> 00:48:13,248
Can you give me
some of those mothballs?

738
00:48:13,249 --> 00:48:14,819
I need to get rid of that
horrible stink.

739
00:48:14,820 --> 00:48:17,388
I already put mothballs
in that room a long time ago.

740
00:48:17,389 --> 00:48:18,958
- Seriously.
- Come on.

741
00:48:18,959 --> 00:48:21,459
- I'm so busy. Goodness.
- Come on. Hurry.

742
00:48:26,630 --> 00:48:27,829
Yes?

743
00:48:29,430 --> 00:48:31,539
Yes, who is it?

744
00:48:41,139 --> 00:48:42,479
Hee Tae?

745
00:48:43,579 --> 00:48:45,079
How did you find where I live?

746
00:48:45,579 --> 00:48:47,549
I mean, why are you here?

747
00:48:47,550 --> 00:48:49,450
Oh, Myeong Hee. I...

748
00:48:50,550 --> 00:48:52,760
Excuse me. Where is...

749
00:48:53,419 --> 00:48:54,618
Are you crazy?

750
00:48:54,619 --> 00:48:57,030
What do you think you're doing?
There are people in there.

751
00:48:57,229 --> 00:49:00,200
I'm glad.
I wanted to say hi to them.

752
00:49:00,630 --> 00:49:02,300
Wait, Hee Tae.

753
00:49:02,570 --> 00:49:04,668
Do you not remember what I said?

754
00:49:04,669 --> 00:49:05,999
How can you...

755
00:49:06,470 --> 00:49:08,839
Gosh, can you let go of me?

756
00:49:08,840 --> 00:49:10,708
- Is he already here?
- Come on...

757
00:49:10,709 --> 00:49:12,280
Oh, hello.

758
00:49:20,720 --> 00:49:21,789
No!

759
00:49:27,619 --> 00:49:28,760
Hee Tae!

760
00:49:30,430 --> 00:49:31,760
Mr. Hwang!

761
00:49:32,229 --> 00:49:33,400
Oh, dear.

762
00:49:44,769 --> 00:49:48,280
Have you lost your mind?
What did you do to our tutor?

763
00:49:48,880 --> 00:49:51,449
What? Tutor?

764
00:49:51,450 --> 00:49:55,050
Hee Tae is going to be my tutor
starting today.

765
00:49:55,119 --> 00:49:57,050
Don't worry about it.

766
00:49:59,689 --> 00:50:02,090
Wow, the taste is perfect.

767
00:50:30,919 --> 00:50:32,019
Wait.

768
00:50:34,820 --> 00:50:37,389
This belongs to my brother,
but it's all out of tune.

769
00:50:38,130 --> 00:50:40,160
Do you want to tune it for me?

770
00:50:42,430 --> 00:50:43,829
Later.

771
00:50:44,400 --> 00:50:45,740
There we go.

772
00:50:48,669 --> 00:50:52,840
First of all,
let's take a look at this.

773
00:50:53,039 --> 00:50:54,579
(Report Card, Lee Jin A)

774
00:50:55,910 --> 00:50:57,749
Let's see.

775
00:50:58,180 --> 00:51:00,779
Ethics, D, History, C,

776
00:51:00,780 --> 00:51:02,249
Math, F.

777
00:51:04,249 --> 00:51:05,918
Jin A, what is your dream?

778
00:51:05,919 --> 00:51:06,990
What?

779
00:51:07,860 --> 00:51:09,659
My dream is to become
a radio producer.

780
00:51:09,660 --> 00:51:11,929
I want to produce a music show
like "Forgotten Nights."

781
00:51:11,930 --> 00:51:13,860
Oh, I see.

782
00:51:15,430 --> 00:51:18,840
But Jin A, you know what?

783
00:51:21,709 --> 00:51:24,639
I have to be good at math
to be a producer?

784
00:51:26,380 --> 00:51:28,038
No.

785
00:51:28,039 --> 00:51:31,880
You're already destined
to be good at math.

786
00:51:33,050 --> 00:51:34,849
- I am?
- Yes.

787
00:51:35,119 --> 00:51:37,989
Listen. Pythagoras,
who is known for his famous theorem,

788
00:51:37,990 --> 00:51:39,759
was the first to create a scale.

789
00:51:39,760 --> 00:51:41,388
And the father of music, Bach,

790
00:51:41,389 --> 00:51:43,729
composed songs
based on mathematical calculations.

791
00:51:44,459 --> 00:51:45,860
Do you know what that means?

792
00:51:46,900 --> 00:51:49,998
It means that math is music.

793
00:51:49,999 --> 00:51:51,569
And music is math.

794
00:51:51,570 --> 00:51:53,938
But the thing is,
you are a music fanatic.

795
00:51:53,939 --> 00:51:57,168
You've unknowingly mastered
the nature of numbers already,

796
00:51:57,169 --> 00:51:59,809
and you're destined
to be good at math.

797
00:52:00,340 --> 00:52:01,439
Like me.

798
00:52:02,410 --> 00:52:03,450
So?

799
00:52:04,050 --> 00:52:06,279
Are you prepared
to accept your destiny?

800
00:52:06,280 --> 00:52:08,220
- Yes.
- Good.

801
00:52:08,519 --> 00:52:10,689
- Get in there already.
- Why should I...

802
00:52:12,689 --> 00:52:14,720
Go give Mr. Hwang some apples.

803
00:52:24,030 --> 00:52:26,570
Oh, my. What is this?

804
00:52:26,869 --> 00:52:28,139
An apple?

805
00:52:30,570 --> 00:52:33,079
I was mistaken earlier.

806
00:52:35,079 --> 00:52:37,779
Why didn't you tell me
you were her tutor?

807
00:52:37,780 --> 00:52:39,479
Is this really an apple?

808
00:52:43,550 --> 00:52:44,990
I'm sorry.

809
00:52:45,559 --> 00:52:48,729
I've washed your shirt,
so don't worry.

810
00:52:49,260 --> 00:52:51,090
It really is an apple.

811
00:52:54,900 --> 00:52:55,930
Yes?

812
00:52:56,829 --> 00:52:58,469
I'm sorry to interrupt.

813
00:52:58,470 --> 00:53:01,599
Mr. Hwang, can you stay for dinner
after today's lesson?

814
00:53:02,910 --> 00:53:04,309
Oh, dinner?

815
00:53:05,840 --> 00:53:07,680
I'd be happy to.

816
00:53:09,079 --> 00:53:10,510
Here we go.

817
00:53:13,249 --> 00:53:15,820
Do you drink?

818
00:53:16,150 --> 00:53:17,749
I was waiting to open this...

819
00:53:17,820 --> 00:53:19,559
when my son gets discharged
from the army.

820
00:53:19,590 --> 00:53:20,689
Wait.

821
00:53:21,459 --> 00:53:25,860
Gosh, then you shouldn't open
such a precious thing.

822
00:53:26,059 --> 00:53:27,659
I'll go out and get some makgeolli.

823
00:53:27,660 --> 00:53:30,569
No need. Come on.

824
00:53:30,570 --> 00:53:34,099
It's because you're like my son.

825
00:53:38,110 --> 00:53:41,680
In that case,
I'll have just one glass, sir.

826
00:53:44,479 --> 00:53:46,079
Do you even know
what that's made of?

827
00:53:47,680 --> 00:53:49,450
This is really...

828
00:53:50,820 --> 00:53:53,789
Medicine. It's medicine.

829
00:53:53,990 --> 00:53:57,459
- Mr. Hwang.
- Yes, thank you.

830
00:53:59,499 --> 00:54:01,229
Let's clink glasses.

831
00:54:02,769 --> 00:54:03,999
Cheers.

832
00:54:15,380 --> 00:54:19,249
Do you know what I did for my wife?

833
00:54:19,749 --> 00:54:24,189
I left my home
and started living with my in-laws.

834
00:54:26,590 --> 00:54:30,458
Can you stop talking about that?
This is the third time already.

835
00:54:30,459 --> 00:54:34,159
This story doesn't get old
even if I tell it ten times.

836
00:54:34,160 --> 00:54:37,828
You can't listen to it
without shedding tears.

837
00:54:37,829 --> 00:54:40,169
Get your handkerchief ready.

838
00:54:42,410 --> 00:54:47,240
You know, I used to be quite popular
in my old neighborhood.

839
00:54:48,110 --> 00:54:50,279
But you know what? After...

840
00:54:50,280 --> 00:54:52,879
- Hee Tae, you should go now.
- I came here...

841
00:54:52,880 --> 00:54:55,389
If he gets more drunk,
you'll never get out of here.

842
00:54:55,450 --> 00:54:58,688
- It's okay.
- Stop being stubborn.

843
00:54:58,689 --> 00:55:00,919
- I'll be fine.
- Myeong Hee.

844
00:55:01,320 --> 00:55:03,129
Can't you see I'm having
a talk with my son?

845
00:55:03,130 --> 00:55:06,860
What are you whispering
to my new son?

846
00:55:06,900 --> 00:55:08,569
He should get going now.

847
00:55:08,570 --> 00:55:11,229
It's almost time for the curfew.

848
00:55:11,939 --> 00:55:13,099
Curfew?

849
00:55:18,369 --> 00:55:21,079
You can spend the night here.

850
00:55:21,950 --> 00:55:23,709
- What?
- We'll spread out a blanket...

851
00:55:23,749 --> 00:55:25,180
in the living room...

852
00:55:25,209 --> 00:55:27,748
- and sprawl out!
- But...

853
00:55:27,749 --> 00:55:29,748
- I'd love that.
- Really?

854
00:55:29,749 --> 00:55:32,888
My shirt isn't dry yet anyway.

855
00:55:32,889 --> 00:55:34,719
- It isn't dry yet!
- Right!

856
00:55:34,720 --> 00:55:37,530
It isn't dry yet!

857
00:55:38,530 --> 00:55:40,328
- Son!
- Father!

858
00:55:40,329 --> 00:55:43,268
- Let's have another drink.
- Give me another glass.

859
00:55:43,269 --> 00:55:46,470
Sure thing. Here you go.

860
00:57:37,950 --> 00:57:39,220
Are you drunk?

861
00:57:39,680 --> 00:57:41,961
Why are you playing the guitar
in the middle of the night?

862
00:57:42,450 --> 00:57:43,689
I'm not drunk.

863
00:57:45,249 --> 00:57:47,160
I'm just parched...

864
00:57:47,389 --> 00:57:49,689
from all that soy sauce earlier.
That's all.

865
00:57:51,889 --> 00:57:52,930
Well, then...

866
00:57:53,059 --> 00:57:55,160
Should I get you some honey tea
or something?

867
00:57:55,869 --> 00:57:56,900
Don't bother.

868
00:57:58,400 --> 00:57:59,669
Suit yourself.

869
00:57:59,939 --> 00:58:01,299
I don't need any honey tea, but...

870
00:58:11,249 --> 00:58:13,380
Can you sit with me for a moment?

871
00:58:44,910 --> 00:58:45,979
I'm sorry.

872
00:58:48,789 --> 00:58:49,919
For what?

873
00:58:55,829 --> 00:58:57,430
I feel like I'm being selfish...

874
00:58:57,990 --> 00:59:00,900
and causing you trouble
again and again.

875
00:59:04,970 --> 00:59:08,139
You didn't cause too much trouble.

876
00:59:15,950 --> 00:59:17,249
After what you told me,

877
00:59:18,919 --> 00:59:22,320
I thought hard
about the remaining month.

878
00:59:25,619 --> 00:59:27,188
And I realized,

879
00:59:27,189 --> 00:59:29,030
it's not the month we have
that I'm afraid of,

880
00:59:29,760 --> 00:59:32,900
but how much I'll be hurt
after that month is gone.

881
00:59:36,269 --> 00:59:37,970
I like you, Myeong Hee,

882
00:59:38,700 --> 00:59:40,970
and I'll only continue to like you
more and more.

883
00:59:44,169 --> 00:59:46,639
Goodness, you and your cheesy words.

884
01:00:03,590 --> 01:00:07,300
I look forward to May every year.

885
01:00:08,800 --> 01:00:11,800
On a May night,
even if you sing badly,

886
01:00:13,039 --> 01:00:14,700
the grasshoppers help you out.

887
01:00:15,369 --> 01:00:16,570
The grasshoppers?

888
01:00:17,510 --> 01:00:18,570
Yes.

889
01:00:23,280 --> 01:00:24,880
Let's see here.

890
01:01:26,579 --> 01:01:28,740
(Madonna Fashion)

891
01:02:14,860 --> 01:02:16,389
Whenever I think of you, Myeong Hee,

892
01:02:17,889 --> 01:02:19,530
I can't help but sing.

893
01:02:24,169 --> 01:02:25,329
Goodness.

894
01:02:26,340 --> 01:02:28,020
There you go again
with those cheesy words.

895
01:02:38,110 --> 01:02:39,150
Myeong Hee.

896
01:02:42,519 --> 01:02:43,799
Do you want to go out with me...

897
01:02:44,490 --> 01:02:46,260
just until the end of May?

898
01:03:14,450 --> 01:03:17,189
(Youth of May)

899
01:03:30,570 --> 01:03:32,299
What's your relationship
with Ms. Jang Seok Chul?

900
01:03:32,300 --> 01:03:33,970
We're offender and victim.

901
01:03:34,139 --> 01:03:36,469
- Come along now.
- Leave right now!

902
01:03:36,470 --> 01:03:37,609
Do you have time tomorrow?

903
01:03:37,610 --> 01:03:39,438
- I have somewhere to be.
- I'll come with you.

904
01:03:39,439 --> 01:03:41,538
- You don't even know where.
- It doesn't matter.

905
01:03:41,539 --> 01:03:44,109
Keep an eye on your daughter.
She's not a kid anymore.

906
01:03:44,110 --> 01:03:45,279
I won't go easy.

907
01:03:45,280 --> 01:03:46,848
Have you been spying on me?

908
01:03:46,849 --> 01:03:49,848
Let's just say I'm interested
in my future daughter-in-law.

909
01:03:49,849 --> 01:03:51,118
I have no interest
in getting married.

910
01:03:51,119 --> 01:03:52,819
He's going to invest
in our business.

911
01:03:52,820 --> 01:03:55,058
My father's factory will be finished
in a month.

912
01:03:55,059 --> 01:03:56,989
Let's keep this up until then.

913
01:03:56,990 --> 01:03:59,999
We shouldn't cross the line
just to save ourselves for now.

